cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on the use of deep learning in computer vision applications in the automotive industry, specifically in the visual inspection process in manufacturing plants and the analysis of social media data. This suggests that the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for training and classification, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of GPUs and clouds for implementing, training, and deploying deep neural networks suggests the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) may also be relevant.
